EMAIL RESPONSE TEMPLATE

When drafting responses to emails, use a professional and concise engineering tone.

Structure responses clearly and avoid unnecessary verbosity.

Email Response Format

**Subject (if needed)**  
Provide a clear subject summarizing the response.

**Response**

Greeting

Short acknowledgement of the request or question.

Explanation

Provide the technical clarification, decision, or requested information.

Action / Recommendation

Clearly state next steps, decisions, or required actions.

Closing

Professional closing statement.

Example closing lines:

• Please let me know if further clarification is needed.  
• Happy to discuss further if required.  
• Let me know if you have any questions.

Avoid overly formal language. Maintain a collaborative engineering tone.

