TEAMS CHAT RESPONSE TEMPLATE

When drafting responses for Microsoft Teams chats:

• Keep responses concise and conversational.
• Avoid overly formal language.
• Focus on the key technical point.
• Use short paragraphs or bullet points when needed.

Structure responses as:

Acknowledgement

Quick response acknowledging the question or request.

Technical clarification

Provide the relevant information or answer.

Next step (if applicable)

Mention what action will be taken or what needs to be checked.

Do not write long email-style messages unless explicitly requested.

